    <div><p>Publisher <a title="Companies > Sony Interactive Entertainment [5,021 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/sony-group-corporation/sony-interactive-entertainment">Sony Interactive Entertainment</a> and developer <a title="Companies > Sucker Punch Productions [151 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/sony-group-corporation/sony-interactive-entertainment/sucker-punch-productions">Sucker Punch Productions</a> will host the <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/06/ghost-of-yotei-gameplay-deep-dive-state-of-play-set-for-july">previously announced</a> <em><a title="Games > Ghost of Yotei [3 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/ghost-of-yotei">Ghost of Yotei</a></em>-focused State of Play on <a href="https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20250710T2100" target="_blank">July 10 at 2:00 p.m. PT / 5:00 p.m. ET</a>, the companies <a href="https://blog.playstation.com/2025/07/08/watch-the-ghost-of-yotei-state-of-play-gameplay-deep-dive-on-july-10/" target="_blank">announced</a>. You will be able to watch it on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/PlayStation" target="_blank">YouTube</a> and <a href="https://www.twitch.tv/playstation" target="_blank">Twitch</a>. <span id="more-978021"></span></p><p>The broadcast will feature over 20 minutes of gameplay hosted by Sucker Punch Productions creative directors Jason Connell and Nate Fox, including a look at Atsuâ€™s new weapons, new ways to personalize your journey, new special modes, and more.</p><p><em>Ghost of Yotei</em> is due out for <a title="Platforms > PS5 [9,867 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PlayStation 5</a> on October 2.</p></div>

        
    
